from directed_graphs.datasets import sink_graph, visualize_heatmap
num_nodes = 35
num_clusters = 7
data = sink_graph(n_points=num_nodes, num_clusters=num_clusters)[0] # somehow get the data
visualize_heatmap(data.edge_index)

from torch_geometric.utils import to_networkx
from node2vec import Node2Vec

# the dataset must be converted to networkx format for node2vec
G_nx = to_networkx(data, to_undirected=False)
node2vec_model = Node2Vec(G_nx, dimensions=2, p=1, q=1, walk_length=20, num_walks=1000, workers=4)
model = node2vec_model.fit(window=1)
emb = model.wv[[str(i) for i in range(num_nodes)]]
emb.shape

class BackwardsNode2Vec[source]

BackwardsNode2Vec(graph, backward_discount=0.1, **kwargs) :: Node2Vec

Node2Vec with added backward edges and backward discount The weights on the original edges would be backward_discount times greater than the weights on the ghost backward edges

from torch_geometric.utils import to_networkx

G_nx = to_networkx(data, to_undirected=False)
node2vec2_model = BackwardsNode2Vec(G_nx, backward_discount=0.1, dimensions=2, walk_length=20, num_walks=1000, workers=4)
emb = node2vec2_model.get_embeddings(window=1)
emb.shape

backward_discount = 0.1, dimension = 2, walk_length = 20, num_walks = 1000, window = 1
